---
/**
 * Deadweight loss from a market intervention (e.g. a per-unit tax).
 * Shows demand and supply, the competitive equilibrium, and how a tax
 * wedge reduces the traded quantity. Consumer surplus, producer surplus
 * and tax revenue are shaded, and the deadweight-loss triangle (lost
 * mutually beneficial trades) is highlighted.
 *
 * Used in Eco 1BACH · Unit 5 (elasticity, surplus and welfare).
 */
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 800 520" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-labelledby="pm-title pm-desc">
  <title id="pm-title">Pérdida de eficiencia (peso muerto) de un impuesto</title>
  <desc id="pm-desc">Mercado con oferta y demanda en el que un impuesto introduce una cuña fiscal que reduce la cantidad intercambiada. Se sombrean el excedente del consumidor, el excedente del productor y la recaudación, y se resalta el triángulo del peso muerto, el bienestar que deja de generarse.</desc>
  <defs>
    <style>
      .bg { fill: #FBF6EC; }
      .axis { stroke: #5C4A3D; stroke-width: 1.5; fill: none; }
      .demand { stroke: #C44E2C; stroke-width: 2.6; fill: none; }
      .supply { stroke: #D4A24C; stroke-width: 2.6; fill: none; }
      .guide { stroke: #8A7868; stroke-width: 1; stroke-dasharray: 4 4; fill: none; }
      .cs { fill: #DBEDED; fill-opacity: 0.85; }
      .ps { fill: #F5E5BC; fill-opacity: 0.7; }
      .rev { fill: #FBE3D6; fill-opacity: 0.9; }
      .dwl { fill: #9C3A1C; fill-opacity: 0.28; stroke: #9C3A1C; stroke-width: 1.4; }
      .axis-label { font-family: 'Switzer', sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.2px; text-transform: uppercase; fill: #5C4A3D; }
      .axis-letter { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 17px; font-weight: 500; fill: #2A1F18; }
      .area-label { font-family: 'Switzer', sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; fill: #2A1F18; text-anchor: middle; }
      .curve-label { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 500; font-style: italic; }
      .point-label { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; font-style: italic; fill: #2A1F18; }
      .dwl-label { font-family: 'Switzer', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; fill: #9C3A1C; }
      .tick { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; fill: #5C4A3D; }
      .has-tip { cursor: help; }
    </style>
    <marker id="pm-arrow" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="10" refX="9" refY="3" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0, 10 3, 0 6" fill="#5C4A3D"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>
  <rect class="bg" x="0" y="0" width="800" height="520"/>

  <!-- Geometry. Plot x:100..700, y:60..420.
       Demand: (130,90) -> (660,400).  Supply: (130,400) -> (660,90).
       Equilibrium E*: intersection at (395,245). P* line y=245.
       Tax shifts effective trade to Qt (left of Q*): Qt at x=300.
       At Qt: price on demand (consumer) Pc and on supply (producer) Pp.
       Demand at x=300: y = 90 + (300-130)/(660-130)*(400-90) = 90 + 170/530*310 = 90+99.4 = 189
       Supply at x=300: y = 400 - (300-130)/530*310 = 400 - 99.4 = 301 -->

  <!-- Consumer surplus: triangle above P*, under demand, left of E* -->
  <path class="cs has-tip" d="M 130 90 L 395 245 L 130 245 Z"><title>Excedente del consumidor: la diferencia entre lo que los compradores estaban dispuestos a pagar y lo que pagan de verdad. Con el impuesto, esta zona se reduce.</title></path>
  <!-- Producer surplus: triangle below P*, above supply, left of E* -->
  <path class="ps has-tip" d="M 130 400 L 395 245 L 130 245 Z"><title>Excedente del productor: la diferencia entre el precio que reciben los vendedores y el mínimo al que estarían dispuestos a vender. El impuesto también lo recorta.</title></path>
  <!-- Tax revenue: rectangle between Pc (189) and Pp (301) up to Qt (x=300) -->
  <rect class="rev has-tip" x="130" y="189" width="170" height="112"><title>Lo que recauda el Estado: el impuesto por unidad multiplicado por las unidades que se siguen vendiendo (Qt). Es una transferencia, no una pérdida: ese dinero financia el gasto público.</title></rect>
  <!-- Deadweight loss triangle: between Qt and Q*, bounded by D and S -->
  <path class="dwl has-tip" d="M 300 189 L 395 245 L 300 301 Z"><title>El peso muerto: bienestar que desaparece sin que lo gane nadie. Son los intercambios que habrían beneficiado a comprador y vendedor pero que el impuesto impide que ocurran.</title></path>

  <!-- Axes -->
  <line class="axis" x1="100" y1="420" x2="725" y2="420" marker-end="url(#pm-arrow)"/>
  <line class="axis" x1="100" y1="440" x2="100" y2="50" marker-end="url(#pm-arrow)"/>
  <text class="tick" x="92" y="436" text-anchor="end">0</text>

  <!-- Axis titles -->
  <text class="axis-letter" x="735" y="425">Q</text>
  <text class="axis-letter" x="92" y="48" text-anchor="end">P</text>
  <text class="axis-label" x="412" y="475" text-anchor="middle">CANTIDAD</text>
  <text class="axis-label" x="40" y="240" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 40 240)">PRECIO</text>

  <!-- Curves -->
  <line class="demand" x1="130" y1="90" x2="660" y2="400"/>
  <line class="supply" x1="130" y1="400" x2="660" y2="90"/>

  <!-- Equilibrium guides -->
  <line class="guide" x1="100" y1="245" x2="395" y2="245"/>
  <line class="guide" x1="395" y1="245" x2="395" y2="420"/>
  <circle cx="395" cy="245" r="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#2A1F18" stroke-width="2.4"/>

  <!-- Tax wedge guides at Qt -->
  <line class="guide" x1="100" y1="189" x2="300" y2="189"/>
  <line class="guide" x1="100" y1="301" x2="300" y2="301"/>
  <line class="guide" x1="300" y1="189" x2="300" y2="420"/>

  <!-- Price/quantity labels -->
  <text class="point-label" x="92" y="250" text-anchor="end">P*</text>
  <text class="point-label" x="92" y="194" text-anchor="end" fill="#9C3A1C">Pc</text>
  <text class="point-label" x="92" y="306" text-anchor="end" fill="#A87A2A">Pp</text>
  <text class="point-label" x="300" y="440" text-anchor="middle">Qt</text>
  <text class="point-label" x="395" y="440" text-anchor="middle">Q*</text>
  <text class="point-label" x="408" y="240">E*</text>

  <!-- Curve labels -->
  <text class="curve-label" x="668" y="403" fill="#C44E2C">D</text>
  <text class="curve-label" x="668" y="92" fill="#A87A2A">O</text>

  <!-- Area labels -->
  <text class="area-label" x="225" y="190" fill="#1F6E6E">EC</text>
  <text class="area-label" x="225" y="335" fill="#A87A2A">EP</text>
  <text class="area-label" x="215" y="250">Recaudación</text>

  <!-- DWL callout -->
  <line class="guide" x1="335" y1="245" x2="470" y2="180" stroke="#9C3A1C"/>
  <text class="dwl-label" x="478" y="170">Peso muerto</text>
  <text class="dwl-label" x="478" y="186" font-size="10.5" font-weight="500">(pérdida de eficiencia)</text>
</svg>
